General Motors has announced its decision to sell operations in South Africa. CAPE TOWN - General Motors Co, which has been manufacturing vehicles in South Africa since 1926, announced its decision to sell operations in the country.It's understood the move was a global decision and Isuzu will be taking over at least half of its production.General Motors South Africa president and managing director Ian Nicholls explains in the audio below.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)